# 📈 Stock Finder | Business and Price Overview

**Stock Finder** is a high-performance, web-based financial analytics terminal built with **Python** and **Streamlit**. It transforms raw market data into institutional-grade business intelligence, providing users with instant sector classification, price performance trends, and a regex-powered "Business Crux" summary.

---

## 🚀 Core Features

- **Smart Entity Resolution:** Leverages `yfinance` to resolve natural language company names (e.g., "Infosys", "ITC Ltd") into global ticker symbols automatically.
- **Institutional UI:** A professional "Financial Terminal" interface featuring **Verdana** typography, high-contrast black-on-white metrics, and a dynamic market-themed background.
- **Business Crux Engine:** A custom text-processing logic that extracts the top 5 strategic business points from dense corporate descriptions, ensuring 100% readability with no text overlapping.
- **Visual Analytics:** Real-time 1-Year Price Performance charts and performance sparklines.
- **Mobile Responsive:** Designed to provide a seamless experience across desktop and mobile browsers.

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

- **Language:** Python 3.x
- **Framework:** [Streamlit](https://streamlit.io/)
- **Data Source:** [Yahoo Finance API (yfinance)](https://github.com/ranaroussi/yfinance)
- **Regex & Logic:** Python `re` module for intelligent text summarization.
- **Styling:** Custom CSS Injection (Glassmorphism & Financial Terminal Aesthetics).

